---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Manifesto | RealityFoundation" active="about">
  <div class="pb-8 border-b mb-10" style="border-color: var(--color-line);">
    <p class="mb-3 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest" style="color: var(--color-muted);">Manifesto</p>
    <h1>Reality is not optional</h1>
  </div>

  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <p>
      We are living through a quiet epistemological crisis. The tools to
      generate convincing images, video, and audio from nothing now exist in
      every pocket. What took a Hollywood studio in 2005 takes a teenager in
      2025. The gap between what is real and what is plausible has collapsed.
    </p>
    <p>
      This is not a technology problem in the narrow sense. It is a problem of
      evidence. Legal systems, journalism, insurance, medicine, and democratic
      accountability all depend — explicitly or implicitly — on the assumption
      that visual records are faithful transcriptions of events. That assumption
      is no longer safe.
    </p>
    <h2>The specific failure</h2>
    <p>
      The failure is not detection. Detection methods exist and improve. The
      failure is <strong>provenance</strong>: the absence of an unbroken,
      independently verifiable chain from capture to presentation. Without
      provenance, even authentic images can be credibly denied. Detection can
      establish that an image has not been manipulated; only provenance can
      establish where it came from.
    </p>
    <h2>What we believe</h2>
    <p>
      We believe that provenance is a public good that no single company can or
      should own. We believe that the scientific foundations of digital
      authenticity must be built in the open, peer-reviewed, and accessible to
      the courts, regulators, and civil society organisations that need them. We
      believe that the window to establish these foundations before the problem
      becomes unmanageable is narrow.
    </p>
    <h2>What we are doing</h2>
    <p>
      RealityFoundation exists to build those foundations. We will publish the
      research. We will engage with regulators. We will train the researchers.
      We will do the slow work that the problem demands and the commercial
      incentive structure does not reward.
    </p>
    <p><strong>Reality is not optional. Evidence must be.</strong></p>
  </div>

  <div style="margin-top:var(--space-12);">
    <a href="/research" class="btn btn-primary"
      >Read the research programme &rarr;</a
    >
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
